<br>
The only reason saddam &quot;may&quot; be holding down extremists is that his government is socialist, not muslim. &quot;That&quot; is why the extremists were against him -- &quot;be cause he was not muslim. ... and yes that is why Osama didnt like him, but you are right, he will support Iraq against America.<br>
<br>
Remember the text of his last message? He called the govenment of Iraq &quot;socialists.&quot;<br>
<br>
Another thing that has begun to anger me a little.... the european attitude. This has caused me to do a little thinking and just a small amount of research (very small).<br>
<br>
It seems that the European Union (EU) was formed with several objectives in mind - two of the most notable were to try to and become more of an economic power and take away some of that power from the US. The second, they were beginning to see that the US was going to become the most powerful nation in the world and wanted to have an organization that was powerful enough to counter it. <br>
<br>
A strong united europe would be able to do that. Its not hard to see this in the recent actions by some of the old guard europeans. This whole big argument is pure politics. The french, germans, and belgians have been stalemating us, not because of what they say in public, but because they are flaunting there power. This seriously alarmed the rest of europe, hence the decsion to let the NATO defense committee decide whether to send aid to Turkey - a committee that france is not part of anymore. ... and did ya notice one more thing? As soon as france was blocked from having a vote, germany and belgium changed there minds. The french must be very good bullies. Its amazing how quickly the other two changed their minds when france was out of the picture.<br>
<br>
A couple of more items to loosely back up these opinions:<br>
<br>
When Jimmy Carter was given the Nobel Peace prize, there was one little bit that wasnt given much air time -- one of the members of the committee that grants the peace prize, a european, stated one of the reasons Carter was given the prize was as an insult to the Bush middle eastern policy. Dont get me wrong. I think Carter was a great choice. I just find it funny what gets air time and what doesnt.<br>
<br>
Next, I was watching MSNBC last nite as they were interviewing people in Paris about this whole US / france thing; and even though a few of those interviewed expressed favorable attitudes towards the US, one person, a french congressman, stated blatantly that the US has to learn that just because it is the most economically and militarily powerful nation on earth, that it cannot just &quot;do what it wants.&quot;<br>
<br>
That even further bolsters my belief that this is politics and not reality. Unfortunately, the reals issues are being ignored.<br>
<br>
Oh yea, there was one more thing I saw in the show i did not like. The reporter went to a bookstore and showed the covers of several books. One book that was written compared present day America to Hitler; another was titled &quot; Why we love to hate Americans,&quot; or something like that.<br>
<br>
Bottom line:<br>
<br>
